This paper focuses on improving internet video streaming through the use of a continual learning algorithm. It involves the use of neural networks to predict transfer times for video chunks, and evaluates the algorithm's performance on a public website that streams live TV. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.LG (Machine Learning), or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses joint selection of congestion-control and bitrate-selection algorithms, which could place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control).
